It unlocks the bootloader, which is awesome, and installs clockworkmod recovery, and installs the latest stable cyanogenmod. While this is geared towards Novices, it leaves them with no way to restore their previous stock roms easily, leaving me with a broken install of cyanogenmod.  I had to learn how to use fastboot to load a factory image I downloaded from Google's website, and then was able to restore it that way, not noobie friendly in the slightest.
